        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 24 at 2:53PM PDT by NWS Elko NV</headline>
        <description>At 253 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 12
miles northwest of Tuscarora, moving east at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Chicken Creek Summit.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
